Duties
The appointee will work on the development of functional polymers for various healthcare and medical applications. He/she will work in a result-oriented and efficient team that is responsible for:
Development of formulations for industrial plastics / rubbers / films applications via functional additive compounding / molding process or organic synthesis;
Characterization of the functional plastics/rubbers using universal material testing machine, FTIR,TGA, DSC, HDT, GPC, etc.;
Evaluation of the mechanical and heat properties and functional performances of the formulations;
Drafting proposals, project progress reports, meeting slides, SOPs, and IP documents;
Incubating ideas to explore the opportunity of cooperation with industry partners;
Collaborating with other research staff on R&D work;
Facilitating the daily operations of the laboratory; and
Performing other duties assigned by supervisor.
Requirements
Master or Ph.D. degree in Polymer Science / Engineering, Chemical / Material Engineering or related disciplines;
Master degree holder with at least 1 year of relevant industrial experience, or fresh PhD graduate from a well-recognized university (which is among the top 100 universities for STEM-related subjects) is an advantage;
Solid knowledge in plastic, film and rubber processing such as PET, PU or liquid silicone rubber;
Hands-on experiences in various types of R&D work, especially in industrial plastics/rubbers/film related projects;
Knowledge and extensive experience in plastic/rubber processing and engineering (e.g. extrusion, film casting, injection molding) is an advantage;
Work independently and able to communicate in teamwork;
Positive, analytical, critical thinking and good troubleshooting skill;
Have a sense of ownership for his/her work;
Willing to work under pressure; and
Good command of English and Chinese, articulate report writing/presentation skills as well as abilities in literature/patent search.
Salary and Benefits
We offer 5-day work, attractive remuneration package to the successful candidates. Salary will be commensurate with qualifications and experience. Medical and dental benefits as well as annual leave will be provided. We also offer an open, collaborative and friendly working environment as well as ample capacity for your professional development. Appointment will be offered on a contract basis, renewable subject to mutual agreement and performance.

Application Procedure
APPLY NOW. We thank applicants for their interests, but advise that only shortlisted candidates will be notified of the results of their applications.
(Applicants who do not hear from us within 8 weeks may consider their application unsuccessful and their data will be destroyed within 24 months of receipt.)

Duties
The appointee will work on the development of porous materials and functional ceramic materials, such as ceramic foam, super-high temperature thermal insulation materials et al. He/she will work in a dynamic and efficient team which is responsible for R&D work, including experimental design, laboratory equipment operation, sample preparation, properties characterization, data analysis, performance testing, drafting proposals / meeting slides / reports / SOP / IP documents, in the following areas:
Developing formulations for porous materials and functional ceramic;
Characterizations and testing at different process stages and evaluating the material performance;
Applying the composite to form prototype to achieve desired functions;
Incubating idea to explore the opportunity of cooperation with industry partners;
Scaling up process for trial production; and
Performing other duties assigned by supervisor.
Requirements

PhD in Chemistry, Materials Science/Engineering or related disciplines;
Extensive experience in operating conventional TEM, XRD, XRF and SEM;
Solid knowledge in materials science and inorganic chemistry;
Solid experience in data acquisition and image simulation software;
Demonstrated ability to work independently and as part of a team, take initiative and be self-motivated;
Good command of spoken and written English and Chinese;
Good communication, presentation and interpersonal skills, ability of literature and patent review are needed; and
Have a sense of ownership for his/her work and willing to work under pressure.
Salary and Benefits
We offer 5-day work, attractive remuneration package to the successful candidates. Salary will be commensurate with qualifications and experience. Medical and dental benefits as well as annual leave will be provided. We also offer an open, collaborative and friendly working environment as well as ample capacity for your professional development. Appointment will be offered on a contract basis, renewable subject to mutual agreement and performance.

